        "body": "## Summary\n- Repairs #42258 as the canonical fix path for #42213.\n- Keeps the stuck-run recovery scoped to the Control UI chat lifecycle and queued-message flush behavior.\n- Addresses hydrated Greptile findings: do not surface transient background probe failures as user-visible errors, avoid double watchdog scheduling, and remove redundant run-activity writes.\n\n## Credit\nThis continues the contributor work from @siewcapital in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/42258. ClawSweeper should preserve that source attribution when updating the branch.\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.node.test.ts\n- pnpm check:changed\n- Real behavior proof should cover a Control UI chat run that misses its terminal event, recovers idle state via the watchdog/session proof path, reloads history, and flushes a queued follow-up without showing a transient probe error banner.\n\nClawSweeper 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: gitcrawl-1599-fix-register-abortcontroller-for-agent-rpc-runs-so-chat-abort-wo\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/42258\n- Credit: Repair contributor branch for source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/42258 by @siewcapital; preserve source PR attribution in the repaired PR history/body.; Do not edit CHANGELOG.md for normal OpenClaw repair work; keep release-note context in the PR body and eventual squash message.; Agent RPC abort support is already credited/landed via https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/71214 and should not be reopened in this repair.\n- Validation: pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.node.test.ts; pnpm check:changed\n- Replacement reason: ClawSweeper could not update the source PR branch directly, so it opened a writable replacement PR instead.\n- Repair fallback: GitHub rejected the repair branch push because it updates workflow files and the ClawSweeper app token does not have workflows permission\n\nInherited issue-closing references from the source PR:\nCloses #42213\n\nCo-author credit kept:\n- @siewcapital: Co-authored-by: Siew's Capital Jarvis <264786654+siewcapital@users.noreply.github.com>\n\nfish notes: model gpt-5.5, reasoning high; reviewed against ae868b7b18df.\n",
